text: I know I'm a man and Mari would hate me but I do feel bad for her. I'm still not entirely sure why she wanted to kill Trixie over something Trixie had no control over but I'm glad she means no harm now, and that Trixie forgave her. I do wonder if she still has the soul stealing magic though.
author: @Nick-yl4qp

replies.text:
Trixie's birth still caused their mother's death, their father to abandon them, and for Mari to grow up sickly and ill. 

Even if Trixie never intended any of it to happen, she is responsible for a lot of the suffering Mari had to endure all her life.

And to top it off, all she heard about Trixie was how she was living a happy life with a gf and a daughter created with powerful magic, the same magic which Trixie took from Mari at birth.

Mari's resentment isn't really justified, but it is understandable.
